---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import FoundingCTA from "../components/FoundingCTA.astro";

const title = "How I Work — Buyer-Side IT Principles | Ascend Griffin";
const description =
  "How I work with founders: always buyer-side, no vendor kickbacks, transparent milestones, fixed pricing on every engagement. 5 principles, no surprises.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Nav />
  <main class="svc">
    {/* ── Hero ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="svc-hero">
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <aside class="svc-rail">
          <div class="rail-marker">00</div>
          <div class="rail-label">How I work</div>
        </aside>

        <div class="svc-hero-body">
          <p class="svc-epigraph">
            "The terms an advisor refuses to put in writing<br />
            are the terms a client should worry about most."
          </p>

          <h1 class="svc-h1">
            How I work — <em>five principles</em>, no surprises.
          </h1>

          <p class="svc-lede">
            What follows is the contract before the contract. Every engagement — Audit, Discovery, Project Support — runs on these five rules. If any of them is a dealbreaker for your situation, better we both know now than after we've signed.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── Principles ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="svc-section">
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <aside class="svc-rail">
          <div class="rail-marker">01</div>
          <div class="rail-label">The five</div>
        </aside>

        <div class="svc-section-body">
          <h2 class="svc-h2">Five things I won't move on.</h2>

          <ol class="ledger">
            <li class="ledger-item">
              <span class="ledger-num">01</span>
              <div class="ledger-content">
                <h4>I'm always on the buyer's side.</h4>
                <p>No vendor kickbacks. No referral fees. No revenue share with anyone I recommend. If I point you toward a developer, designer, or vendor, it's because they fit your project — not because they fit my pocket. If a vendor offers me a commission for the referral, I disclose it to you and decline it.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="ledger-item">
              <span class="ledger-num">02</span>
              <div class="ledger-content">
                <h4>I price-fix before the work starts.</h4>
                <p>No hourly billing. Fixed or fixed-plus-performance pricing on every engagement. If the scope grows mid-flight, we re-paper the agreement — there's never a quiet "oh, this will be a bit more." That conversation always happens before the work, not after.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="ledger-item">
              <span class="ledger-num">03</span>
              <div class="ledger-content">
                <h4>I never start without discovery.</h4>
                <p>A 30-minute call comes first, always — including for one-page audits. Without that conversation I can't honestly tell you whether I'm the right read for your situation, or whether you'd benefit. If I'm not the right read, I'll say so on the call and usually point you toward someone who is. I'd rather lose the engagement than take work I can't deliver well.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="ledger-item">
              <span class="ledger-num">04</span>
              <div class="ledger-content">
                <h4>I leave a documented trail.</h4>
                <p>Every recommendation goes in writing. Every decision lands in a note. If next month a co-founder, board member, or new hire asks "what did we agree?" — there's a line you can quote. You shouldn't be the only person holding the project context in their head.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="ledger-item">
              <span class="ledger-num">05</span>
              <div class="ledger-content">
                <h4>I never optimize for keeping you longer.</h4>
                <p>When a project is ready to hand off — we hand off. I don't inflate engagements to stay relevant, and I'd rather end an arrangement clean than pad it for the retainer line. The honest version of this work is making yourself replaceable on a known timeline.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── What that means in practice ────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="svc-section svc-section-muted">
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <aside class="svc-rail">
          <div class="rail-marker">02</div>
          <div class="rail-label">In practice</div>
        </aside>

        <div class="svc-section-body">
          <h2 class="svc-h2">What that looks like in practice.</h2>
          <p class="svc-section-lede">
            Three concrete things that follow from the principles above — the parts that usually surprise people on the first engagement.
          </p>

          <div class="prose">
            <p><strong>Conflicts of interest stay on the record.</strong> If I have any relationship — past project, friendship, prior employer — with a vendor under consideration, you'll know about it before the comparison call. Not after. The "by the way" disclosure is exactly the moment to lose trust.</p>

            <p><strong>I'll recommend you not hire me.</strong> Sometimes the right answer is "you don't need an outside read here, you need to talk to your dev team for one hour." I'd rather give you that 15-minute answer for free than charge $1,000 to confirm something you already know.</p>

            <p><strong>The final deliverable is something you can use without me.</strong> Audit reports, discovery briefs, vendor comparison docs — they're written so they hold up if I disappear tomorrow. No dependencies on me being in the room.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── What I expect from clients ─────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="svc-section">
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <aside class="svc-rail">
          <div class="rail-marker">03</div>
          <div class="rail-label">From you</div>
        </aside>

        <div class="svc-section-body">
          <h2 class="svc-h2">What I expect from you.</h2>
          <p class="svc-section-lede">Honest two-way deal.</p>

          <ul class="exclude">
            <li><span class="exclude-mark">—</span><span><strong>Tell me what's actually going on.</strong> Including the parts you'd rather not say out loud yet. The earlier I see the real picture, the more useful I am.</span></li>
            <li><span class="exclude-mark">—</span><span><strong>Decide quickly when I bring you options.</strong> A 5-day delay on a decision is fine. A 5-week delay turns a $4,000 engagement into a $9,000 one.</span></li>
            <li><span class="exclude-mark">—</span><span><strong>Loop me in before you sign vendor paper, not after.</strong> Reading a contract you already signed is a different (worse, more expensive) job.</span></li>
            <li><span class="exclude-mark">—</span><span><strong>Push back when you disagree.</strong> I'm wrong sometimes. The earlier you say it, the better the outcome.</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <FoundingCTA service="discovery" spotsLeft={2} />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .svc { background: radial-gradient(ellipse at top right, rgba(184, 135, 58, 0.04), transparent 50%), radial-gradient(ellipse at bottom left, rgba(184, 135, 58, 0.03), transparent 40%), var(--bg-0); min-height: 100vh; }
  .svc-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr; gap: 64px; max-width: 1120px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 var(--gutter); }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .svc-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 24px; padding: 0 var(--gutter-sm); } }
  .svc-rail { position: sticky; top: 88px; align-self: start; height: fit-content; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-1); padding-top: 14px; }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .svc-rail { position: static; display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 12px; padding-top: 8px; } }
  .rail-marker { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-1); letter-spacing: 0.04em; line-height: 1; }
  .rail-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-3); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; margin-top: 6px; }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .rail-label { margin-top: 0; } }

  .svc-hero { padding: 80px 0 56px; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .svc-hero { padding: 48px 0 32px; } }
  .svc-epigraph { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text-3); font-style: italic; margin: 0 0 32px; padding-left: 18px; border-left: 2px solid var(--accent); max-width: 56ch; }
  .svc-h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(40px, 5.5vw, 68px); line-height: 1.04; letter-spacing: -0.025em; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 28px; font-weight: 700; max-width: 20ch; }
  .svc-h1 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--editorial); font-weight: 700; }
  .svc-lede { font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 32px; max-width: 60ch; }

  .svc-section { padding: 80px 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-1); }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .svc-section { padding: 48px 0; } }
  .svc-section-muted { background: var(--bg-1); }
  .svc-h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(28px, 3.5vw, 40px); line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.015em; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 16px; font-weight: 700; max-width: 24ch; }
  .svc-h2 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--editorial); }
  .svc-section-lede { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 40px; max-width: 60ch; }

  .prose p { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 18px; max-width: 65ch; }
  .prose p strong { color: var(--text-1); font-weight: 600; }

  .ledger { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-1); }
  .ledger-item { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 64px 1fr; gap: 24px; padding: 28px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-1); align-items: start; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .ledger-item { grid-template-columns: 40px 1fr; gap: 16px; padding: 24px 0; } }
  .ledger-num { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 24px; color: var(--accent-pressed); font-weight: 600; line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .ledger-content h4 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 8px; line-height: 1.35; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.005em; }
  .ledger-content p { font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0; max-width: 60ch; }

  .exclude { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .exclude li { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 16px; padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--border-1); color: var(--text-2); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.55; }
  .exclude li:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .exclude-mark { font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--text-4); font-size: 18px; line-height: 1; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .exclude strong { color: var(--text-1); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
